{# ─── Chart 2 · Power Law Implied CAGR vs. S&P 500 ────────────────── #}
<section class="gallery-section" id="section-cagr" aria-labelledby="title-cagr">
    <div class="gallery-section-inner">
        <header class="gallery-section-header">
            <p class="gallery-section-eyebrow">&sect;I &middot; The Model &middot; Chart 2 of 10</p>
            <h2 id="title-cagr" class="gallery-section-title">Bitcoin's Power Law Implied CAGR vs. the S&amp;P 500</h2>
            <p class="gallery-section-subtitle">What the model projects, year by starting year, against the equity benchmark.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="gallery-chart-frame">
            <canvas id="galleryCagrChart" aria-label="Power Law implied CAGR vs S&P 500 bar chart"></canvas>
            <div class="gallery-chart-fallback" aria-hidden="true">
                <p class="chart-loading">Loading the comparison&hellip;</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gallery-section-prose">
            <p>The Power Law implies a specific annualized return from each starting year. Each bar is the model's projected CAGR through 2035 for a bitcoin purchase made in that year; the dashed line is the S&amp;P 500's historical ~10% annual average. Even at the conservative end &mdash; buying in 2030 &mdash; the model's implied CAGR through 2035 is roughly <em>three times</em> the equity benchmark.</p>
            <p class="prose-footnote"><em>On convergence:</em> Bitcoin's implied CAGR declines as the model decelerates, but at every starting year on this chart it remains more than 2&times; the S&amp;P 500's 10% benchmark. Even projecting out to the year 2150, bitcoin's implied annualized return &mdash; though steadily decreasing &mdash; still sits above 10%. The chart's window shows the strongest period of relative outperformance; the gap, while shrinking, persists for over a century beyond it.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="gallery-section-source">More in this exploration &rarr; <a href="/the-power-law.html">Bitcoin &amp; the Power Law</a></p>
    </div>
</section>


{# ═══ §II · REAL-WORLD DENOMINATIONS ═══════════════════════════════ #}

{# ─── Chart 3 · BTC Required to Buy the Median US House ──────────── #}
<section class="gallery-section" id="section-btc-house" aria-labelledby="title-btc-house">
    <div class="gallery-section-inner">
